n raised the standardized test score by 0.14 standard deviations an integrated strategy involving all three factors was most effective having an impact of 0.20 standard devi ations this is partly because peer tutoring and parental communi cation work as complementary inputs in the underlying production function for learning download pdf+ complete modified february 2011 pdf 221_ _peer_tutoring pdf 296.9 kb topics china stanford university all rights reserved 650 723 2300 terms of use copyright complaints rss+ rss xml feeds
